# Systematic Styling

This is a single-file app (`index.html`) but it should be treated with the same discipline as a component-based project.

## Rules

### 1. Use CSS custom properties for repeated values
Colours, spacing, radii and z-index layers are already used in multiple places. Define them once, reference everywhere.

```css
/* ✅ Define at top of <style> */
:root {
  --color-primary: #1e3a5f;
  --color-accent:  #10b981;
  --color-danger:  #ef4444;
  --radius-card:   12px;
  --z-sticky:      100;
}

/* ❌ BAD: repeating the same hex in 12 places */
background: #1e3a5f;
```

### 2. No one-off inline styles for layout
`style="..."` on elements is acceptable only for dynamic values set by JavaScript. Static layout and appearance must use a named CSS class.

```html
<!-- ❌ BAD -->
<div style="display:flex;gap:8px;align-items:center">

<!-- ✅ GOOD -->
<div class="row-actions">
```

### 3. Reuse existing classes before creating new ones
Before adding a new class, search the stylesheet for a class that already does the same thing. Extend with a modifier if needed.

### 4. New UI patterns need a named shell/template
When adding a new recurring UI element (modal, card, row, badge), define a base class for it even if there is currently only one instance — that is the template for future instances.

### 5. Think before each change
Ask: "Will this change scale if there are 10 of these? Will the next developer (or future me) understand why this value exists?"
